8 1951 PA 51, MCL 247.663c.
9 (c) "Local grade separation fund" means the local grade
10 separation fund created by section 11i of 1951 PA 51, MCL 247.661i.
11 (d) "Neighborhood roads funds" means the neighborhood roads
12 fund created by section 13c of 1951 PA 51, MCL 247.663c.
13 (e) "State trunkline fund" means the state trunkline fund
14 created by section 11 of 1951 PA 51, MCL 247.661.
15 Sec. 802. At the close of the fiscal year, any unencumbered
16 and unexpended balance in the neighborhood roads fund not
17 previously allocated under section 13c(5)(a) to (e) of 1951 PA 51,
18 MCL 247.663c, remains in the neighborhood roads fund and carries
19 forward and is appropriated to local road agencies and the state
20 trunkline fund according to section 13c(5) of 1951 PA 51, MCL
21 247.663c.
22 Sec. 803. (1) At the close of the fiscal year, any
23 unencumbered and unexpended balance in the movable bridge fund
24 remains in the movable bridge fund and carries forward and is
25 appropriated for the purposes described in section 11g(3)(b) of
26 1951 PA 51, MCL 247.661g.
27 (2) As used in this section, "moveable bridge fund" means the
28 moveable bridge fund created by section 11g of 1951 PA 51, MCL
29 247.661g.
ERE S06125'26 (S-5) sr2e15

44
1
2 DEPARTMENT OF TREASURY
3 Sec. 901. (1) The Medicaid caseload reserve fund is created in
4 the state treasury. The purpose of the fund is to support Medicaid
5 caseload costs that occur at levels above appropriated amounts.
6 (2) Money may be spent from the fund only on appropriation.
7 (3) The state treasurer shall deposit money and other assets
8 received under section 702 or from any other source in the fund.
9 The state treasurer shall direct the investment of money in the
10 fund and credit interest and earnings from the investments to the
11 fund.
12 (4) Money in the fund at the close of the fiscal year remains
13 in the fund and does not lapse to the general fund.
14 (5) As used in this section, "fund" means the Medicaid
15 caseload reserve fund created by subsection (1).
16 Sec. 902. (1) The HR-1 costs fund is created within the state
17 treasury. The purpose of the fund is to support costs that occur as
18 a result of administering or implementing the 2025 budget
19 reconciliation act, Public Law 119-21.
20 (2) Money may be spent from the fund only on appropriation.
21 (3) The state treasurer shall deposit money and other assets
22 received under section 703 or from any other source in the fund.
23 The state treasurer shall direct the investment of money in the
24 fund and credit interest and earnings from the investments to the
25 fund.
26 (4) Money in the fund at the close of the fiscal year remains
27 in the fund and does not lapse to the general fund.
28 (5) As used in this section, "fund" means the HR-1 costs fund
29 created by subsection (1).
ERE S06125'26 (S-5) sr2e15

45
1
2 DEPARTMENT OF MILITARY AND VETERANS AFFAIRS
3 Sec. 1001. (1) Funds appropriated in part 1 for Selfridge Air
4 National Guard Base must be used to support costs of runway
5 encroachment solutions while complying with air installation
6 compatible use zone program recommendations, including, but not
7 limited to, all of the following:
8 (a) Capital improvements necessary to shift the runway to the
9 north and repair the airfield and nonairfield features of the base
10 and surrounding community impacted by the shift.
11 (b) Infrastructure projects including, but not limited to,
12 roadways repairs, vehicle access to the base and to the museum,
13 stormwater drain and culvert repairs and modernization, force
14 protection features, airfield features, and taxiway extensions.
15 (2) The funds appropriated in part 1 for Selfridge Air
16 National Guard base may be spent only if the state budget director
17 determines that funds sufficient to make necessary improvements to
18 Selfridge Air National Guard base as described under subsection (1)
19 were not appropriated under Senate Bill No. 865 of the 103rd
20 Legislature for the fiscal year ending September 30, 2026.
21 (3) Unexpended funds appropriated in part 1 for Selfridge Air
22 National Guard Base are designated as a work project appropriation.
23 Unencumbered or unallotted funds shall not lapse at the end of the
24 fiscal year and shall be available for expenditures under this
25 section until the project has been completed. The following is in
26 compliance with section 451a of the management and budget act, 1984
27 PA 431, MCL 18.1451a:
28 (a) The purpose of the project is to support costs of runway
29 encroachment solutions.
ERE S06125'26 (S-5) sr2e15

46
1 (b) The project will be accomplished by utilizing state
2 employees, contracts with service providers, or both.
3 (c) The total estimated cost of the project is
4 $152,000,000.00.
5 (d) The tentative completion date is September 30, 2027.
6 Sec. 1002. (1) The department shall identify 1 or more of the
7 following methods for funding Selfridge Air National Guard Base
8 under part 1:
9 (a) Unobligated work project account balances associated with
10 the strategic outreach and attraction reserve fund created in
11 section 4 of the Michigan trust fund act, 2000 PA 489, MCL 12.254,
12 or other lapsed account balances determined by the state budget
13 director.
14 (b) Unobligated general fund/general purpose or federal
15 appropriations that are eligible to support Selfridge Air National
16 Guard Base infrastructure improvements.
17 (c) Special obligation bond financing through the Michigan
18 strategic fund created in section 5 of the Michigan strategic fund
19 act, 1984 PA 270, MCL 125.2005.
20 (2) The department must make every effort to fully utilize the
21 funding options and available revenues identified in subsection
22 (1). After identifying 1 or more of the funding sources under
23 subsection (1) and amounts available from those funding sources
24 that will be used to support Selfridge Air National Guard Base, the
25 department shall identify any remaining costs.
26 (3) Pursuant to section 352 of the management and budget act,
27 1984 PA 431, MCL 18.1352, there is appropriated from the
28 countercyclical budget and economic stabilization fund created
29 under section 351 of the management and budget act, 1984 PA 431,
ERE S06125'26 (S-5) sr2e15

47
1 MCL 18.1351, an amount equal to the amount identified by the
2 department under subsection (2) to support remaining costs for
3 Selfridge Air National Guard Base appropriated in part 1. The
4 annual growth rate for the current calendar year was estimated to
5 be less than 0% at the most recent consensus revenue estimating
6 conference.
